1
00:00:03,330 --> 00:00:06,168
(panting heavily)

2
00:00:06,252 --> 00:00:09,426
They said it wasn't
going to rain today...

3
00:00:17,984 --> 00:00:19,404
Heh

4
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:26,527
(Startled with heavy breathing)

5
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:28,153
(suspense)

6
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:29,300
(confused)

7
00:00:30,968 --> 00:00:32,805
Ran!

8
00:00:33,557 --> 00:00:35,352
Conan-kun, Dad...

9
00:00:35,853 --> 00:00:38,274
You came to pick me up.
Thank you.

10
00:00:38,358 --> 00:00:40,988
Geez, it's already past nine.

11
00:00:41,072 --> 00:00:43,911
Sorry, club ran late.

12
00:00:43,994 --> 00:00:45,289
Here, umbrella.

13
00:00:45,372 --> 00:00:46,875
Thanks, Conan-kun.

14
00:00:46,958 --> 00:00:47,960
Tch...

15
00:00:48,629 --> 00:00:54,641
♪~

16
00:01:01,655 --> 00:01:05,371
Slicing through black shadows
and dark gloom is the light of deduction.

17
00:01:05,454 --> 00:01:09,295
A string of robberies,
a chance prank, an unexpected turn.

18
00:01:09,379 --> 00:01:10,840
Seeing through to the one and only truth.

19
00:01:10,923 --> 00:01:12,844
A child in appearance, with the mind of an adult.

20
00:01:12,927 --> 00:01:15,599
His name is Detective Conan!

21
00:02:37,346 --> 00:02:43,358
~♪

22
00:02:46,728 --> 00:02:52,628
"Coincidences Come in Twos"

23
00:02:52,628 --> 00:02:54,042
Be careful out there.

24
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:58,008
Word is there's been
some nasty business around here lately.

25
00:02:58,091 --> 00:03:00,764
Yeah, that hooded
robber, right?

26
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,183
Let's see...

27
00:03:02,266 --> 00:03:04,313
They call him the Hood Man.

28
00:03:04,396 --> 00:03:08,195
He attacks women with an expandable baton
and snatches their bags, right?

29
00:03:08,571 --> 00:03:12,579
Yeah, so far everyone's
gotten off with minor injuries, but...

30
00:03:12,662 --> 00:03:15,919
if they don't catch him soon,
the attacks are gonna escalate...

31
00:03:16,002 --> 00:03:17,464
Kyaa!
Huh?

32
00:03:17,547 --> 00:03:18,633
Hm?

33
00:03:22,891 --> 00:03:24,686
Ow, ow...

34
00:03:24,770 --> 00:03:25,897
Hey, you okay?

35
00:03:26,649 --> 00:03:28,986
The hooded guy went that way...

36
00:03:29,070 --> 00:03:30,407
Got it.

37
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:33,413
Hey, mister.
Uh...

38
00:03:34,247 --> 00:03:35,417
Conan-kun?

39
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:38,756
How come you're not wet?
Your clothes, mister.

40
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:39,842
Huh?

41
00:03:41,094 --> 00:03:43,098
What's wrong, Conan-kun?

42
00:03:43,349 --> 00:03:44,852
We gotta hurry or the culprit'll...

43
00:03:45,353 --> 00:03:47,357
The rain that started suddenly.

44
00:03:47,816 --> 00:03:50,864
His shoes are dirty,
his pants are soaked.

45
00:03:51,197 --> 00:03:53,828
And yet he's got no umbrella,
but his clothes...

46
00:03:53,911 --> 00:03:56,249
aren't wet. That's weird, isn't it?

47
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,463
Yeah, you're right.
Ugh...

48
00:03:58,921 --> 00:04:03,221
Mister, weren't you wearing
something else over that a minute ago?

49
00:04:03,306 --> 00:04:07,481
Like, say...
a hooded jacket?

50
00:04:07,564 --> 00:04:09,943
Damn it!
Stop right there!

51
00:04:10,027 --> 00:04:11,447
Out of my way!

52
00:04:12,407 --> 00:04:14,703
Hyah!
Gwaah...

53
00:04:18,168 --> 00:04:20,381
Heh, yeah, figured
it'd end up like this.

54
00:04:21,383 --> 00:04:23,387
Hey, you okay?

55
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:25,057
I'm fine over here.

56
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:26,226
Not you.

57
00:04:26,602 --> 00:04:28,481
Hm? Oh, more importantly...

58
00:04:28,564 --> 00:04:31,654
The person who screamed earlier?
Oh, this way.

59
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:33,574
Huh?

60
00:04:36,455 --> 00:04:38,250
Miss, are you okay?

61
00:04:40,421 --> 00:04:42,258
Ngh, ugh...

62
00:04:49,648 --> 00:04:52,445
Really, you saved us, Mouri-kun.

63
00:04:52,904 --> 00:04:55,743
The Hood Man's been
giving us a real headache.

64
00:04:56,160 --> 00:05:00,043
Ah, all in a day's work, Inspector.

65
00:05:00,127 --> 00:05:01,505
Nyahaha...

66
00:05:01,922 --> 00:05:05,012
Shh, this is a hospital.

67
00:05:05,095 --> 00:05:07,309
Huh? Pipe down,
I know that.

68
00:05:07,392 --> 00:05:08,978
Heh, hahaha...
Well then, Inspector.

69
00:05:09,061 --> 00:05:12,192
If anything else comes up,
contact me anytime. Yes.

70
00:05:12,276 --> 00:05:13,321
Uh...

71
00:05:14,906 --> 00:05:16,785
Thank you so much.

72
00:05:16,869 --> 00:05:18,372
Excuse me.

73
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:20,668
How did it go?

74
00:05:21,127 --> 00:05:24,968
She's fine. No abnormalities
on the CT or the EEG...

75
00:05:25,052 --> 00:05:27,097
and the doctor says
she can go home.

76
00:05:27,181 --> 00:05:28,183
Thank goodness.

77
00:05:28,726 --> 00:05:30,688
Thank you so much.
- Tachibana Mizuki (25), victim.

78
00:05:30,772 --> 00:05:32,442
It's all thanks to everyone.

79
00:05:32,525 --> 00:05:33,527
Oh, right.

80
00:05:33,611 --> 00:05:35,740
I should call my roommate.

81
00:05:35,823 --> 00:05:37,827
She's probably worried.

82
00:05:38,161 --> 00:05:41,167
Still, I'm glad
it was just a minor injury.

83
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,506
A blessing in disguise, I'd say.

84
00:05:43,589 --> 00:05:44,966
(phone buzzing)
Oh.

85
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:47,931
Sorry, excuse me a second.

86
00:05:48,599 --> 00:05:50,102
Yes, Sato speaking.

87
00:05:50,185 --> 00:05:53,359
That's strange...
Huh? What's wrong?

88
00:05:53,442 --> 00:05:57,450
Yoko, my roommate,
isn't answering the phone.

89
00:05:57,534 --> 00:06:00,038
She should've gotten
off work ages ago.

90
00:06:00,122 --> 00:06:01,417
Huh?
Hm?

91
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,423
A woman's body found
near the scene from earlier?

92
00:06:05,048 --> 00:06:07,470
Yes... yes.

93
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:11,937
Mizuki-san, do you know
what this Yoko was wearing?

94
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:13,607
Huh? Let's see...

95
00:06:13,691 --> 00:06:17,030
A white jacket
and a beige skirt, I think...

96
00:06:17,824 --> 00:06:20,078
Tachibana-san,
is that true?

97
00:06:20,496 --> 00:06:23,084
Uh... yes. Oh...

98
00:06:23,168 --> 00:06:25,840
H-hey, don't tell me...

99
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:28,387
No way...

100
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:30,850
What a mess.

101
00:06:37,356 --> 00:06:39,525
- Katsuragi Youko (25), Mizuki's roommate.

102
00:06:41,747 --> 00:06:45,212
There's no mistake.
It's Yoko.

103
00:06:45,546 --> 00:06:47,467
(crying)

104
00:06:47,550 --> 00:06:51,517
This morning when we said goodbye,
she was perfectly fine...

105
00:06:51,809 --> 00:06:56,192
I never thought that
would be the last time.

106
00:06:56,443 --> 00:06:58,238
Yoko!

107
00:06:58,322 --> 00:06:59,950
(crying)

108
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:01,202
Mizuki-san...

109
00:07:01,495 --> 00:07:04,459
Ran, stay with her.

110
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:15,523
Judging by the body's condition,
she's been dead one to two hours, I'd say.

111
00:07:15,606 --> 00:07:16,733
Yeah.

112
00:07:17,067 --> 00:07:21,326
She worked at an apparel shop
nearby...

113
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:23,956
and it seems she was attacked
on her way home from work.

114
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:27,839
She was struck on the back
of the head with a rod-like object.

115
00:07:27,922 --> 00:07:32,640
The Hood Man's known method,
the area, the time of day...

116
00:07:32,724 --> 00:07:33,976
it all matches.

117
00:07:34,477 --> 00:07:37,775
The cash was also taken from the victim's wallet.

118
00:07:37,984 --> 00:07:42,327
He probably intended to leave her
with minor injuries like the others...

119
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:45,958
but something set him off
and he ended up killing Yoko.

120
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:51,177
Then, before the rush wore off,
he attacked Mizuki-san.

121
00:07:51,470 --> 00:07:53,181
Hmm...

122
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:57,105
Who'd have thought roommates
would be attacked one after the other.

123
00:07:57,565 --> 00:08:01,113
But that's what led to
the culprit's arrest.

124
00:08:01,531 --> 00:08:03,410
Maybe the bond between them...

125
00:08:03,494 --> 00:08:06,708
is what brought about
such a miracle.

126
00:08:09,923 --> 00:08:11,843
Hm... what's this?

127
00:08:13,722 --> 00:08:15,351
(sniffing)

128
00:08:15,434 --> 00:08:17,981
The smell of coffee... hm?

129
00:08:20,736 --> 00:08:22,072
This is...

130
00:08:22,155 --> 00:08:23,157
Whoa!

131
00:08:23,575 --> 00:08:26,289
This brat, snooping
around again...

132
00:08:26,373 --> 00:08:27,375
Ahaha...

133
00:08:27,834 --> 00:08:29,879
Huh, where's everyone going?

134
00:08:30,673 --> 00:08:34,723
We're going to ask Tachibana-san
some questions down at HQ too.

135
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:37,895
We need to take her statement
about her own case as well.

136
00:08:38,187 --> 00:08:41,027
I figured I'd go
along with Mizuki-san.

137
00:08:41,445 --> 00:08:45,411
Oh, I wanna come too!
That's okay, right, mister?

138
00:08:45,494 --> 00:08:47,039
Mm...
Heheh.

139
00:08:51,631 --> 00:08:55,138
Just to confirm,
the one who attacked you...

140
00:08:55,681 --> 00:08:57,935
was that man, correct?

141
00:09:01,401 --> 00:09:04,156
Yes, it was definitely him.

142
00:09:04,824 --> 00:09:05,951
Understood.

143
00:09:06,453 --> 00:09:08,957
Hey, isn't that guy mad about something?

144
00:09:09,041 --> 00:09:11,546
Ah, him...

145
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:15,805
He confessed readily
to the string of robberies, but...

146
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:19,854
he stubbornly refuses to admit
to killing Yoko-san.

147
00:09:20,146 --> 00:09:22,360
He says he attacked Tachibana-san...

148
00:09:22,443 --> 00:09:26,284
only because she saw his face and
he panicked, not knowing what to do...

149
00:09:26,368 --> 00:09:28,789
and that he never intended to kill anyone.

150
00:09:28,872 --> 00:09:30,376
Huh.

151
00:09:30,584 --> 00:09:32,547
Hey, what's the meaning of this?

152
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:35,218
Tell us.
Hey, are you listening?

153
00:09:35,302 --> 00:09:37,515
Detective.
No, like I said...

154
00:09:37,598 --> 00:09:39,059
We're currently searching...

155
00:09:39,143 --> 00:09:40,896
What's going on, Detective Takagi?

156
00:09:41,272 --> 00:09:43,652
Ah, Conan-kun. Well...

157
00:09:43,735 --> 00:09:46,575
So you caught him, right?
The Hood Man.

158
00:09:46,908 --> 00:09:48,912
Are you ladies, by any chance...

159
00:09:49,121 --> 00:09:51,793
That's right,
victims of the Hood Man.

160
00:09:51,877 --> 00:09:54,256
You're going to get them back
for us, right?

161
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:55,759
Our wallets.

162
00:09:55,843 --> 00:09:57,930
Mine had my license in it...

163
00:09:58,014 --> 00:09:59,350
Are you really even looking?

164
00:09:59,434 --> 00:10:01,061
We are searching.
Hold on a sec.

165
00:10:01,479 --> 00:10:04,234
You ladies all had
your whole wallets taken?

166
00:10:04,319 --> 00:10:05,571
Yes, that's right.

167
00:10:06,364 --> 00:10:07,825
What's going on here?

168
00:10:07,909 --> 00:10:11,625
Yoko-san, who was killed,
only had her cash taken...

169
00:10:12,042 --> 00:10:14,631
and her wallet was left
behind at the scene.

170
00:10:15,841 --> 00:10:18,639
Alright, Takagi-kun,
I'll leave them to you.

171
00:10:18,722 --> 00:10:20,976
Right, I'll see them off properly.

172
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,396
Wait, Detective Sato.

173
00:10:22,772 --> 00:10:23,774
Hm?

174
00:10:24,024 --> 00:10:25,945
There's a thread on your skirt.

175
00:10:26,028 --> 00:10:27,907
No way, ugh.

176
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:30,371
The basting thread
was still on it.

177
00:10:30,454 --> 00:10:32,123
Basting thread?

178
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:35,129
On the slits of a brand-new
skirt and the like...

179
00:10:35,213 --> 00:10:37,969
there's a thread called basting thread.

180
00:10:38,052 --> 00:10:41,016
(snipping)
So the fabric doesn't shift...

181
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:44,607
see, like this,
the end is knotted...

182
00:10:44,691 --> 00:10:46,110
and it's lightly tacked in place.

183
00:10:46,319 --> 00:10:47,321
Oh...

184
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:51,496
The skirt I wore today
got torn...

185
00:10:51,579 --> 00:10:53,333
so I bought this new one in a hurry.

186
00:10:56,171 --> 00:10:58,385
So that's how it is.

187
00:11:08,385 --> 00:11:09,930
(phone ringing)
Ah.

188
00:11:10,306 --> 00:11:12,268
Yes, Mouri here.

189
00:11:12,728 --> 00:11:14,355
Inspector.

190
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,652
What, really?

191
00:11:17,571 --> 00:11:19,157
Yes, understood.

192
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:21,746
(call ending)
Did something happen?

193
00:11:22,748 --> 00:11:26,087
The blood on the Hood Man's
expandable baton...

194
00:11:26,171 --> 00:11:28,676
has been confirmed
to be Yoko-san's.

195
00:11:28,926 --> 00:11:31,473
What?
Then that means...

196
00:11:31,556 --> 00:11:34,020
Yeah, we've got
physical evidence now...

197
00:11:34,103 --> 00:11:37,569
so the Hood Man's confirmed
as Yoko-san's killer too.

198
00:11:37,819 --> 00:11:39,907
That's good to hear, Mizuki-san.

199
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:44,123
Yes, I'm sure Yoko is
happy up in heaven.

200
00:11:47,088 --> 00:11:50,177
Phew... ate my fill.

201
00:11:50,552 --> 00:11:53,893
Miss, another beer
and some fried chicken.

202
00:11:53,976 --> 00:11:56,147
Come on, give it a rest.

203
00:11:56,231 --> 00:11:59,529
What's the harm?
The case is solved.

204
00:11:59,613 --> 00:12:02,577
I'm telling you to read
the time and place.

205
00:12:02,661 --> 00:12:05,625
Mizuki-san just lost
her best friend.

206
00:12:05,709 --> 00:12:07,713
Now, now, you two...

207
00:12:07,796 --> 00:12:10,259
Heheh, hehe...

208
00:12:10,342 --> 00:12:12,681
Oh, I'm sorry.

209
00:12:12,764 --> 00:12:15,477
Yoko and I used to fight...

210
00:12:15,562 --> 00:12:18,024
and chat here all the time too...

211
00:12:18,108 --> 00:12:20,446
so it just brought back memories.

212
00:12:20,529 --> 00:12:22,074
Mizuki-san...

213
00:12:22,701 --> 00:12:25,623
But I'm glad
the culprit was caught.

214
00:12:25,707 --> 00:12:27,961
It really is thanks to all of you.

215
00:12:28,044 --> 00:12:30,466
Ngh, ugh...

216
00:12:30,549 --> 00:12:32,804
(nose blowing)
Hey, wait, Dad.

217
00:12:32,888 --> 00:12:36,937
That's my hand towel.
Yours is over there.

218
00:12:37,021 --> 00:12:38,482
Huh, it is?

219
00:12:38,566 --> 00:12:40,527
Geez, unbelievable.

220
00:12:40,612 --> 00:12:42,949
Sorry, sorry. Here, take it back.

221
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:46,247
Ew, no way I can
use it like this.

222
00:12:46,331 --> 00:12:49,671
Huh? What's the big deal?
It's basically the same thing.

223
00:12:49,755 --> 00:12:51,299
Totally different.

224
00:12:51,382 --> 00:12:55,015
I see... so that's how it was.

225
00:12:56,644 --> 00:12:59,691
No, you mustn't, Tachibana-san.

226
00:13:00,275 --> 00:13:04,367
Please, let me get this.
As a token of my thanks.

227
00:13:04,618 --> 00:13:08,166
No, it'll cause problems
for us later. You understand.

228
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:10,045
Is that so?

229
00:13:10,128 --> 00:13:13,343
Sorry. Well then,
I'll take you up on it.

230
00:13:13,886 --> 00:13:16,349
That'll be 10,250 yen.

231
00:13:16,432 --> 00:13:19,313
Huh? That added up
to quite a bit.

232
00:13:19,397 --> 00:13:20,733
You... gonna be okay?

233
00:13:20,817 --> 00:13:22,528
Thanks for the meal.

234
00:13:22,612 --> 00:13:24,156
Sorry about that, Takagi.

235
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:33,759
Thank you so much, really.

236
00:13:34,051 --> 00:13:38,184
Um, I know it's hard,
but please hang in there.

237
00:13:38,268 --> 00:13:41,024
If you ever get lonely,
contact me anytime.

238
00:13:41,107 --> 00:13:44,573
I'll come running.
Ow, ow, ow...

239
00:13:44,656 --> 00:13:47,453
Sorry, don't worry about it.

240
00:13:47,871 --> 00:13:50,960
Heheh... well then,
I'll be going.

241
00:13:52,046 --> 00:13:54,801
Ngh...
Whoa, wha...

242
00:13:54,885 --> 00:13:56,471
Huh?
Dad?

243
00:14:01,022 --> 00:14:02,149
Mouri-san?

244
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:04,655
The pain finally
woke me up.

245
00:14:04,988 --> 00:14:07,117
This case isn't over yet.

246
00:14:07,577 --> 00:14:10,040
Mouri-san, what do you mean
"not over"?

247
00:14:10,708 --> 00:14:14,841
The one who killed Yoko-san
wasn't the Hood Man.

248
00:14:14,925 --> 00:14:18,641
What are you talking about?
The evidence just came in...

249
00:14:18,975 --> 00:14:21,563
No, if he were the culprit...

250
00:14:21,647 --> 00:14:23,149
there's something that doesn't add up.

251
00:14:23,734 --> 00:14:25,028
Something that doesn't add up?

252
00:14:25,487 --> 00:14:28,869
The cash was taken
from Yoko-san's wallet...

253
00:14:28,953 --> 00:14:32,334
and the wallet itself was
left behind at the scene.

254
00:14:32,669 --> 00:14:35,507
But money was
the goal, right?

255
00:14:35,842 --> 00:14:37,929
No. In the previous three cases...

256
00:14:38,013 --> 00:14:41,394
the culprit always stole
the entire wallet.

257
00:14:41,477 --> 00:14:43,649
Why was this time
the only exception?

258
00:14:44,191 --> 00:14:48,241
It's certainly odd,
but that alone...

259
00:14:48,951 --> 00:14:51,039
Next, the wound on the body.

260
00:14:51,330 --> 00:14:54,838
Yoko-san's wound was on
the left side of the back of her head.

261
00:14:55,338 --> 00:14:58,178
Yoko-san was attacked from behind.

262
00:14:58,261 --> 00:15:01,267
Which means the culprit
held the baton in their left hand...

263
00:15:01,350 --> 00:15:04,065
and struck Yoko-san.

264
00:15:04,148 --> 00:15:06,486
In other words,
the culprit is left-handed.

265
00:15:06,945 --> 00:15:08,281
But the Hood Man...

266
00:15:10,285 --> 00:15:12,081
Ah, he's right-handed.

267
00:15:12,624 --> 00:15:14,335
By the way, Mizuki-san...

268
00:15:14,418 --> 00:15:16,632
you made your phone call
with your left hand...

269
00:15:16,715 --> 00:15:20,097
and you tried to pay
with your left hand.

270
00:15:20,472 --> 00:15:21,767
Huh...

271
00:15:22,142 --> 00:15:24,898
It... it's true, I'm left-handed.

272
00:15:25,650 --> 00:15:29,406
But there are plenty of other
left-handed people, aren't there?

273
00:15:30,117 --> 00:15:31,578
There's more.

274
00:15:31,662 --> 00:15:34,458
On the white inner shirt
Yoko-san was wearing...

275
00:15:34,542 --> 00:15:38,049
there was a fresh coffee stain.

276
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:41,097
But the stain stopped
at the line of the skirt...

277
00:15:41,180 --> 00:15:44,228
and there was no stain
on the skirt itself.

278
00:15:44,563 --> 00:15:48,444
And on that skirt,
there was basting thread.

279
00:15:48,779 --> 00:15:50,365
Basting thread?

280
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:53,581
Yes, the kind that's on
brand-new skirts...

281
00:15:53,664 --> 00:15:56,169
to keep the fabric
from shifting...

282
00:15:56,252 --> 00:15:57,714
that basting thread.

283
00:15:58,548 --> 00:16:00,260
Thinking it might be the case...

284
00:16:00,343 --> 00:16:04,226
I checked with the manager
of the shop where Yoko-san worked.

285
00:16:04,853 --> 00:16:09,236
Right before Yoko-san left her
workplace, the apparel shop, today...

286
00:16:09,486 --> 00:16:11,199
she apparently spilled coffee...

287
00:16:11,282 --> 00:16:13,871
on the clothes and skirt
she was wearing.

288
00:16:14,664 --> 00:16:18,672
So she bought a new
jacket and skirt right there...

289
00:16:18,964 --> 00:16:21,093
changed into them,
and left the shop.

290
00:16:22,095 --> 00:16:25,770
That's why the coffee stain on
her shirt cut off partway...

291
00:16:26,354 --> 00:16:30,028
and the basting thread was
still left on the skirt.

292
00:16:30,988 --> 00:16:33,034
And what does that
have to do with anything?

293
00:16:33,869 --> 00:16:37,542
You said this to
Yoko-san's body, didn't you?

294
00:16:38,253 --> 00:16:41,802
This morning when we said goodbye,
she was perfectly fine...

295
00:16:41,885 --> 00:16:45,475
I never thought that
would be the last time.

296
00:16:45,559 --> 00:16:47,605
Yoko!

297
00:16:47,897 --> 00:16:51,697
You only parted with her in the morning
and hadn't seen her since...

298
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:53,826
so how did you know?

299
00:16:54,326 --> 00:16:58,251
The outfit Yoko-san changed
into on her way home from work.

300
00:16:58,334 --> 00:17:00,171
Ah...
Mizuki-san?

301
00:17:00,255 --> 00:17:04,723
I... I'm sure she was wearing
a similar color this morning.

302
00:17:05,015 --> 00:17:06,643
So I just mistook it for...

303
00:17:07,019 --> 00:17:10,943
Mizuki-san, the mister
says to look at this.

304
00:17:12,529 --> 00:17:13,531
Ah...

305
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,037
This is...
What's this...

306
00:17:16,747 --> 00:17:19,001
I had the manager send it to me.

307
00:17:19,084 --> 00:17:23,594
That's a photo of Yoko-san
today, before she changed.

308
00:17:24,428 --> 00:17:26,307
Please tell me, Mizuki-san.

309
00:17:26,557 --> 00:17:29,355
How could that possibly
look like a white jacket...

310
00:17:29,438 --> 00:17:31,568
and a beige skirt?

311
00:17:34,616 --> 00:17:36,787
You met her, didn't you?

312
00:17:37,496 --> 00:17:40,001
Yoko-san, on her way
home from work.

313
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,047
Ah...

314
00:17:42,130 --> 00:17:44,969
But Mouri-san, that alone...

315
00:17:45,053 --> 00:17:48,769
isn't enough to say Mizuki-san
killed Yoko-san, is it?

316
00:17:49,395 --> 00:17:53,069
Yeah, it's true these are
all circumstantial.

317
00:17:53,152 --> 00:17:54,781
Hardly conclusive.

318
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:59,958
That's awful. Treating me
like a criminal over just that...

319
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:02,129
Yoko was my best friend.

320
00:18:02,212 --> 00:18:03,757
That's right, Dad.

321
00:18:03,841 --> 00:18:06,554
If you're going to go that far,
you need solid proof...

322
00:18:07,139 --> 00:18:09,268
Solid proof, eh?

323
00:18:09,351 --> 00:18:12,608
Well, I've got it.
Right here, right now.

324
00:18:12,692 --> 00:18:14,069
Huh?
Ah.

325
00:18:14,571 --> 00:18:16,992
Mizuki-san, at the restaurant...

326
00:18:17,075 --> 00:18:21,250
you took your wallet out of your bag
and, for some reason, put it in your pocket.

327
00:18:21,626 --> 00:18:24,841
Why didn't you put it
back in your bag?

328
00:18:25,258 --> 00:18:28,556
You were scared, weren't you?
That when you put the wallet away...

329
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:31,103
someone would see
what was inside your bag.

330
00:18:32,314 --> 00:18:33,609
Inside your bag...

331
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:38,201
is something you can't let
us see.

332
00:18:38,284 --> 00:18:39,369
Isn't that right?

333
00:18:40,330 --> 00:18:43,044
I thought it was strange
from the start.

334
00:18:43,127 --> 00:18:46,801
Tonight's the kind of chilly evening
you can't go without a jacket...

335
00:18:46,885 --> 00:18:50,016
and yet you're dressed far too lightly.

336
00:18:50,935 --> 00:18:55,485
But if you had a reason
you couldn't wear a jacket...

337
00:18:55,569 --> 00:18:58,157
then your outfit makes sense.

338
00:18:58,951 --> 00:19:03,627
What's in your bag is probably a jacket
splattered with Yoko-san's blood.

339
00:19:03,710 --> 00:19:05,756
Huh...
What?

340
00:19:05,839 --> 00:19:07,259
No, that's not all.

341
00:19:07,802 --> 00:19:11,267
The expandable baton the
Hood Man originally carried...

342
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:13,271
should be in there too.

343
00:19:13,354 --> 00:19:14,566
Ah...

344
00:19:14,899 --> 00:19:18,574
Then the Hood Man...
what he was carrying was...

345
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:23,082
That's the very weapon Mizuki-san
used to kill Yoko-san.

346
00:19:23,374 --> 00:19:24,794
Isn't that right?

347
00:19:26,756 --> 00:19:30,723
First, to make it look like
the Hood Man's doing...

348
00:19:30,806 --> 00:19:34,271
you examined the expandable baton
he used in the string of attacks...

349
00:19:34,354 --> 00:19:36,985
bought the same type...

350
00:19:37,862 --> 00:19:41,786
and killed Yoko-san
with that baton.

351
00:19:42,037 --> 00:19:44,917
But on your way home,
ironically...

352
00:19:45,001 --> 00:19:48,174
you were attacked
by the real Hood Man.

353
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:50,553
Unlucky, wasn't it.

354
00:19:50,804 --> 00:19:55,021
But then a chance came along
to turn that misfortune into fortune.

355
00:19:55,104 --> 00:19:56,566
Hey, you okay?

356
00:19:56,650 --> 00:19:59,614
The hooded guy went that way...

357
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:02,535
In that moment,
you had an idea.

358
00:20:03,454 --> 00:20:06,795
A way to make the most
of the accident...

359
00:20:06,878 --> 00:20:09,884
of being attacked by
the real Hood Man.

360
00:20:11,011 --> 00:20:13,600
I see... so you swapped
your own baton...

361
00:20:13,684 --> 00:20:16,355
with the Hood Man's.

362
00:20:16,438 --> 00:20:19,236
That's why Yoko-san's blood...

363
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:21,700
was on the Hood Man's baton.

364
00:20:23,327 --> 00:20:27,586
Yeah, I almost got
fooled myself.

365
00:20:27,670 --> 00:20:30,341
But that whole hand towel thing
gave me the hint.

366
00:20:31,385 --> 00:20:33,556
The weapon, just like
the hand towels...

367
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:36,520
had been swapped somewhere
along the line.

368
00:20:37,105 --> 00:20:40,486
Mizuki-san, even after
you were rescued...

369
00:20:40,571 --> 00:20:43,284
Ran was with you the entire time.

370
00:20:43,827 --> 00:20:47,500
You wouldn't have had any time
to dispose of the jacket or baton.

371
00:20:47,585 --> 00:20:51,634
Now, please show us
what's inside that bag.

372
00:20:53,972 --> 00:20:55,099
Ah...

373
00:21:00,109 --> 00:21:01,571
Mizuki-san...

374
00:21:04,409 --> 00:21:05,913
You see, Yoko...

375
00:21:06,538 --> 00:21:09,587
was truly like the sun.

376
00:21:10,087 --> 00:21:12,342
Bright, selfish...

377
00:21:12,425 --> 00:21:15,431
always the center
of her own world...

378
00:21:16,141 --> 00:21:20,567
And before that sun,
I was nothing but a powerless moon.

379
00:21:21,527 --> 00:21:23,113
Taking advantage of that...

380
00:21:23,197 --> 00:21:26,245
Yoko always took
everything from me.

381
00:21:26,328 --> 00:21:29,042
My clothes, my money,
the person I loved.

382
00:21:29,585 --> 00:21:32,549
Acting like it was
only natural.

383
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:35,471
And still, I endured it.

384
00:21:37,433 --> 00:21:39,730
Until I heard those words.

385
00:21:40,649 --> 00:21:44,030
Sorry, Mizuki's coming home soon.

386
00:21:44,114 --> 00:21:48,623
Ugh, I wish that girl would just
get done in by the Hood Man or something.

387
00:21:48,832 --> 00:21:52,756
She's such a pain.
Heheh, hahaha...

388
00:21:53,048 --> 00:21:55,553
So I turned it around on her instead.

389
00:21:55,637 --> 00:21:58,017
Made it look like
the Hood Man's doing.

390
00:21:58,350 --> 00:22:03,027
(crying)

391
00:22:03,402 --> 00:22:09,414
♪~

392
00:23:17,801 --> 00:23:23,103
~♪

393
00:23:23,479 --> 00:23:24,732
Hey, Dad.

394
00:23:24,815 --> 00:23:27,988
You snuck a bite again,
didn't you? My cake.

395
00:23:28,072 --> 00:23:31,871
N-no, I didn't.
Sure, it's usually me, but...

396
00:23:31,954 --> 00:23:34,501
this time it really was
that thieving cat...

397
00:23:34,585 --> 00:23:38,885
Huh, pinning the blame
on Goro-chan again.

398
00:23:38,968 --> 00:23:41,808
(punch and Kogoro yelling)

399
00:23:41,891 --> 00:23:42,893
Huh... hm?

400
00:23:44,104 --> 00:23:48,529
Haha... you pulled off
a perfect crime.

401
00:23:48,613 --> 00:23:50,533
(cat meowing)

402
00:23:52,286 --> 00:23:55,417
Ah, so you heard that phone call.

403
00:23:55,877 --> 00:23:59,467
Your collar's stretched out and your underwear's showing.

404
00:23:59,551 --> 00:24:02,891
Oh, th-this is called off-the-shoulder...

405
00:24:02,975 --> 00:24:04,435
I'm showing it on purpose.

406
00:24:04,519 --> 00:24:07,441
Ah, kyaaa!

407
00:24:08,068 --> 00:24:09,195
Drowning, huh.

408
00:24:09,279 --> 00:24:10,574
Huh?

409
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:14,497
I'm placing you under emergency arrest for murder.

410
00:24:14,582 --> 00:24:15,959
Huh?!

411
00:24:15,959 --> 00:24:21,220
Next Conan:
"Makoto Kyogoku, A Suspect? (Part 1)"

412
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:39,020
Next Conan's Hint:

413
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:41,720
"Bowling alley"

414
00:24:41,731 --> 00:24:42,733
At the bowling alley...

415
00:24:42,816 --> 00:24:44,320
Karate vs. Jeet Kune Do
416
00:24:44,403 --> 00:24:45,990
Why there?
